Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Drain @black beans{1}.

In a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings), combine @white rice{½%cup}, tomato, garlic, beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ¾ cup water, @fajita spice blend{1%tsp} (you'll use more later), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} (1 1/2 cups water and 2 tsp Fajita Spice Blend for 4). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{20-22%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Cilantro-Lime Crema ==

While rice cooks, roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, cilantro, and juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings). Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

== Steak ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @fajita spice blend{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. (Use the rest of the Fajita Spice Blend as you like.)

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. TIP: If pork starts to brown too quickly, lower the heat and cover pan.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Finish ==

Fluff rice and beans with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Slice steak crosswise.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Divide rice and beans and steak between plates in separate sections. Pour any resting juices over steak and drizzle with crema. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Slice chicken or steak against the grain.